      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;installation-roadmap&#34;&gt;Installation Roadmap &lt;a href=&#34;#installation-roadmap&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;alert alert-danger d-flex&#34; role=&#34;alert&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;flex-shrink-1 alert-icon&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;span class=&#34;material-icons size-20 me-2&#34;&gt;&#xA;  report&#xA;  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;w-100&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Always consult the &lt;a href=&#34;https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Installation_guide&#34; rel=&#34;external&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Arch Wiki Installation Guide&lt;svg width=&#34;16&#34; height=&#34;16&#34; viewBox=&#34;0 0 24 24&#34; xmlns=&#34;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#34;&gt;&lt;path fill=&#34;currentColor&#34; d=&#34;M14 5c-.552 0-1-.448-1-1s.448-1 1-1h6c.552 0 1 .448 1 1v6c0 .552-.448 1-1 1s-1-.448-1-1v-3.586l-7.293 7.293c-.391.39-1.024.39-1.414 0-.391-.391-.391-1.024 0-1.414l7.293-7.293h-3.586zm-9 2c-.552 0-1 .448-1 1v11c0 .552.448 1 1 1h11c.552 0 1-.448 1-1v-4.563c0-.552.448-1 1-1s1 .448 1 1v4.563c0 1.657-1.343 3-3 3h-11c-1.657 0-3-1.343-3-3v-11c0-1.657 1.343-3 3-3h4.563c.552 0 1 .448 1 1s-.448 1-1 1h-4.563z&#34;/&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for the most current procedures and troubleshooting tips as the installation process may evolve over time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Installation</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/installation/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/installation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;installation&#34;&gt;Installation &lt;a href=&#34;#installation&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;boot-into-the-arch-linux-live-environment&#34;&gt;Boot into the Arch Linux Live Environment &lt;a href=&#34;#boot-into-the-arch-linux-live-environment&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Boot from the USB drive and confirm you are in UEFI mode by checking for the presence of &lt;code&gt;/sys/firmware/efi&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;set-up-the-keyboard-layout-if-needed&#34;&gt;Set Up the Keyboard Layout (if needed) &lt;a href=&#34;#set-up-the-keyboard-layout-if-needed&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can list all available keymaps using:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;7df5172&#34; class=&#34;language- &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;localectl list-keymaps&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Then set your preferred keymap:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;4e79821&#34; class=&#34;language-bash &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;loadkeys us&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;(replace &lt;code&gt;us&lt;/code&gt; with your chosen layout)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Additionally, you can change the console font with:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>System Configuration</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/system-configuration/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/system-configuration/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;system-configuration&#34;&gt;System Configuration &lt;a href=&#34;#system-configuration&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;generate-the-filesystem-table-fstab&#34;&gt;Generate the Filesystem Table (fstab) &lt;a href=&#34;#generate-the-filesystem-table-fstab&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;After installing the base system, generate the filesystem table by running:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;e932261&#34; class=&#34;language-bash &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;genfstab -U /mnt &amp;gt;&amp;gt; /mnt/etc/fstab&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s important to review the generated &lt;code&gt;/mnt/etc/fstab&lt;/code&gt; file to ensure that all partitions are correctly listed and configured.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;chroot-into-the-new-system&#34;&gt;Chroot into the New System &lt;a href=&#34;#chroot-into-the-new-system&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;Finally, change root into your new system environment to continue with further configuration:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;de0c732&#34; class=&#34;language-bash &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;arch-chroot /mnt&lt;/code&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h4 id=&#34;time-zone-and-localization&#34;&gt;Time Zone and Localization &lt;a href=&#34;#time-zone-and-localization&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&lt;p&gt;If you need to &lt;strong&gt;set your timezone manually&lt;/strong&gt; you can do so by creating a symlink:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Post-Installation</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/post-installation/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 19 Feb 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/installation/post-installation/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h3 id=&#34;reboot-and-post-installation&#34;&gt;Reboot and Post Installation &lt;a href=&#34;#reboot-and-post-installation&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;h4 id=&#34;exit-chroot-and-unmount-filesystems&#34;&gt;Exit Chroot and Unmount Filesystems &lt;a href=&#34;#exit-chroot-and-unmount-filesystems&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &#xA;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;prism-codeblock &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;pre id=&#34;4cf65e3&#34; class=&#34;language-bash &#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;code&gt;exit           # exits chroot&#xA;umount -R /mnt # not mandatory but &lt;/code&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/pre&gt;&#xA;  &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;h5 id=&#34;reboot-the-system&#34;&gt;Reboot the System &lt;a href=&#34;#reboot-the-system&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;Run: &lt;code&gt;reboot&lt;/code&gt; and remove the installation media when prompted.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Then, Log in as your regular user.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h5 id=&#34;post-installation-tasks&#34;&gt;Post Installation Tasks &lt;a href=&#34;#post-installation-tasks&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34; aria-hidden=&#34;true&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;material-icons align-middle&#34;&gt;link&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h5&gt;&lt;p&gt;After rebooting and logging in, it&amp;rsquo;s time to fine-tune your system configurations by enabling and starting essential services.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;First, ensure that the network connection remains stable by enabling the network management tool you configured earlier.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
